Cell["\<\
If you want genuine orthogonal representation matrices (i.e., the \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]normal representation\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]), then \
you can simply divide out the square roots of the diagonal elements, but then \
your representation is no longer rational.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->796632200,ExpressionUUID->"98416f01-dc6e-4e7f-b9ea-0148833bc307"]
}, Open  ]],

