   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 59, 43.218506}", 
    "history" -> {"12", "14.2", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "symmetric group", "permutation group", "Young tableaux", 
      "group representation theory"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "N.B. This is a revised copy of the document posted on the Wolfram \
Community by Bernd Guenther with some symbols replaced by those of the same \
functionality. For the accurate accounts, see the original document. This \
tech note explains some computations involving characters and representations \
of the symmetric group. Although elementary in presentation style, it is not \
intended as textbook on representation theory. Conjugacy classes in the \
symmetric group S_n are uniquely determined by cycle decomposition type of \
permutations, i.e. by the lengths of the disjoint cycles composing them, thus \
by a list of integers adding up to n. Such a list of integers, by convention \
listed in decreasing order, is called a partition of n. Hence conjugacy \
classes in and irreducible characters of S_n are in one to one correspondence \
to the partitions of n. We obtain the character table by the function:", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "Characters of the Symmetric Group", "titlemodifier" -> "", 
